baseline_groups.claim_summary: College-educated workers have substantially higher WFH share than non-college workers, with a roughly 18 percentage point gap.
baseline_groups.notes: Baseline regresses wfh_share on college with age, age squared, and female as controls (N=69,373). Descriptive paper, not causal.

global_notes: Survey data release documenting WFH patterns. Several specs use alternative treatments or outcomes that change the estimand. Race variables show collinearity issues. Heterogeneity specs change sample composition.
